#~ msgid ""
#~ "<xref linkend=\"chapter-temporary-tools\"/> also shows you how to build a "
#~ "first pass of the toolchain, including Binutils and GCC (first pass "
#~ "basically means these two core packages will be reinstalled).  The next "
#~ "step is to build Glibc, the C library. Glibc will be compiled by the "
#~ "toolchain programs built in the first pass. Then, a second pass of the "
#~ "toolchain will be built. This time, the toolchain will be dynamically "
#~ "linked against the newly built Glibc. The remaining <xref "
#~ "linkend=\"chapter-temporary-tools\"/> packages are built using this "
